Find the Fourier series representation for the periodic function f(x) given by:

f(x) = 
\begin{cases}
  1,  & \text{if $-\pi < x < 0$ } \\
  -1, & \text{if $0 < x < \pi$} \\
  0, & \text{if $x = -\pi$ or $x = \pi$}
\end{cases}

over the interval $[-\pi,\pi]$. Calculate the first four terms of the Fourier series and plot the function and the Fourier series on the same graph.
